[6] Russia (Zelenograd)
Date: 17 Apr 2013
Source: Zelenograd News Agency [In Russian, translated by Mod.NR]
http://www.zelenograd.ru/news/8906/


An increase in the incidence of measles began in February [2013] and continued until the present. The chief medical officer of Zelenograd Leonid Denisov, is calling the situation "complex." Since the end of February more than 20 people were diagnosed with measles and new cases are being identified. It affects children and adults, including staff of the Zelenograd hospital.

Doctors are trying to vaccinate all who had contact with the infected: co-workers, neighbors. The infected were in contact with more than 1000 people, nearly half of them children, including 60 infants under 1 year old who cannot be vaccinated against measles. 80 percent of children older 1 year old are vaccinated. In total about 2500 people were vaccinated over the past 3 months. [Protective target is 95 percent -- see Comment at end. - Mod.JW]

A Number of the staff in the Zelenograd hospital contracted measles from one of the patients hopsitalised in April. The last outbreak of measles in Zelenograd was recorded in late 2011 - early 2012. Prior to that, from 2008, cases of measles in the county were not recorded

[More than 20 people with measles were registered in Zelenograd, a city in Moscow Province, among them both adults and children. Sincere there were cases of measles infection that took place in the hospital, health personnel should be vaccinated against measles. In addition all adults and children older than 14 years of age (ideally all the seronegative population) should be vaccinated against measles too. Zeelenograd is a city) located 37 kilometres from the centre of Moscow - Mod.VM/CP.]

