[7] Congo DR (Orienale)
Date: Mon 22 apr 2013
Source: Radio Okapi [In French, trans. by corresp. SB, edited]
http://radiookapi.net/en-bref/2013/04/22/province-orientale-82-cas-de-rougeole-signales-en-trois-mois/


82 cases of measles reported in three months in Orientale province
------------------------------------------------------------------
The WHO epidemiologist in charge of emergencies and Humanitarian actions in Orientale Province, Colin Ngobila, said Monday, 22 Apr 2013, that 82 cases of measles have been reported since March [2013] in the Health zones of Duruma, Dungu, Aba and Faradje in Haut-Uele district (Orientale Province). Epidemiologist Ngobila called for a strengthening of the Expanded Vaccination Programme (PEV in French) in these health areas. He declared that: "We promote the proper management of cases including vitamin therapy and we also require strengthening of the routine Systematic PEV, i.e. the PEV routine vaccination that is given to children before their first birthday."

